    <h1>Join Us at IMTS: &quot;Fueling US Manufacturing&quot; with Shawn Fitzgerald &amp; Austin Hennessey from Mitsubishi HC Capital America</h1>
    <div class="legal-meta">Shawn Fitzgerald, Chief Marketing Officer · Monday, September 2, 2024</div>
  </div>

<figure style="max-width:1080px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px"><video src="/articles/imts-presentation-fueling-us-manufacturing-with-mitsibishi-hc-capital-america/1725289448-learn-how-to-stretch-your-continuous-improvement-budget-further-than-ever-before.mp4" autoplay loop muted playsinline style="width:100%;height:auto;display:block"></video></figure>
  <div class="legal-prose">
<p>We&#x27;re thrilled to announce an exciting presentation at the upcoming International Manufacturing Technology Show (IMTS) in Chicago, IL. Shawn Fitzgerald, VP of Sales and Marketing at Formic, and Austin Hennessey from Mitsubishi HC Capital America, will be taking the stage to deliver a compelling talk titled <strong>&quot;Fueling US Manufacturing.&quot;</strong> This must-attend session will take place in the North Building, Level 3, booth #236329, on <strong>Tuesday, September 10th, and Wednesday, September 11th, at 2 PM</strong>.</p> <h3>About the Presentation: Fueling US Manufacturing</h3> <p>In today&#x27;s fast-paced manufacturing environment, one of the most significant challenges is the continuous struggle to fund all the essential improvement projects. Manufacturers are often faced with tough decisions due to limited budgets—there simply isn&#x27;t enough money to do everything that needs to be done. But what if there was a way to stretch those dollars further, enabling more projects, enhancing productivity, improving quality, and ensuring safety, all while keeping some financial &quot;dry powder&quot; for future needs?</p> <p>Shawn and Austin will dive into how Formic and Mitsubishi HC Capital America are partnering to revolutionize the way US manufacturers approach automation and equipment financing. They&#x27;ll explore how manufacturers can leverage innovative financial solutions like &quot;Robots-as-a-Service&quot; (RaaS) from Formic and &quot;Equipment-as-a-Service&quot; from Mitsubishi HC Capital America to overcome traditional financial and operational barriers.</p> <h3>Why You Should Attend</h3> <p>Attending this presentation is a unique opportunity to learn how these services can allow you to deploy automation without the need for large upfront capital investments. Formic’s RaaS model is designed specifically to eliminate the barriers to automation adoption, enabling manufacturers to scale and grow more effectively. Meanwhile, Mitsubishi HC Capital America offers flexible financing options that make it easier than ever to access the industrial equipment you need to drive your business forward.</p> <h3>Bring Your Questions</h3> <p>Whether you’re curious about the specifics of robots-as-a-service, case packing, palletizing, or how equipment-as-a-service financing works, Shawn and Austin are ready to answer all your questions. This is your chance to get expert insights on how these solutions can be tailored to meet the unique needs of your facility.</p> <h3>Don’t Miss Out!</h3> <p>Join us at booth #236329 in the North Building, Level 3, at 2 PM on Tuesday or Wednesday. Learn how you can fuel your manufacturing operations more efficiently and effectively with the right financial and operational strategies. We look forward to seeing you there!</p>
